  "text": "Resistance to As in S. meliloti depends on ars operon which consists of arsR (transcriptional regulator), arsC (arsenate reductase) and aqpS (aquaglyceroporin). The AqpS is the only protein of the S. meliloti ars operon that facilitates transport of arsenite and flows out of the cell [CITATION_1] . Moreover, a protein codified by arsH gene has been described as a nicotinamide adenine dinucleotide phosphate (NADPH): flavin mononucleotide (FMN) oxide-reductase that forms H 2 O 2 in S. meliloti exposed to As [CITATION_2] .",
